article.headline: Bradley 79, Samford 59
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Tony Bennett and Patrick O'Bryant scored 17 points each to lead Bradley to a 79-59 home win over Samford Tuesday night. The Braves (7-1) took a comfortable 42-28 lead into the half, finishing the game with 29-of-57 shooting from the field and 13-of-15 shooting from the free throw line. Leading the Bulldogs (5-4) was Randall Gulina with 17 points, followed by Jerry Smith with 11 and Jon Mills with 10. Samford was 23-of-45 from the field, 9-of-25 from the 3-point line and 4-of-5 from the free throw line.
